FuncDef:
The traffic-analysis tcp export template timeout-rate command sets the delivery interval of the template for exporting packets carrying the TCP flow analysis results of intelligent traffic analysis.
The undo traffic-analysis tcp export template timeout-rate command restores the default configuration. The traffic-analysis tcp export template timeout-rate command sets the delivery interval of the template for exporting packets carrying the TCP flow analysis results of intelligent traffic analysis. The undo traffic-analysis tcp export template timeout-rate command restores the default configuration. By default, the delivery interval of the template for exporting packets carrying the TCP flow analysis results of intelligent traffic analysis is 1 minute. This command is supported only on the CE6860-SAN, CE6866K, CE6866, CE6860-HAM, CE8850-SAN, CE8851K, CE8851-32CQ8DQ-P and CE8850-HAM.
CLIs: undo traffic-analysis tcp export template timeout-rate [ <timeout-interval> ]

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the interval at which the template is delivered.
The value is an integer that ranges from 1 to 60. in minute. The default value is 1.
